'''Kō Shrine''' ({{lang|ja|国府神社}})
* [[Kō Shrine (Takatori)]] - Located in {{ill|Takatori, Nara|en}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|en|12=draft}}. This shrine, situated in Shitakusa, Takatori, is the {{ill|Sōja|en}} (provincial shrine) of {{ill|Yamato Province|en|12=draft}}. It holds a distinguished position along with {{ill|Ōmiwa Shrine|en}}, being a central focus of faith and worship within the province. * [[Kō Shrine (Ichikawa)]] - Found in {{ill|Ichikawa, Chiba|en|12=draft}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|en}}, this ancient shrine was founded on February 8, 1087 (Eihō 7). Also known as Ōtori Ōkami, it enshrines {{ill|Yamato Takeru|en|12=draft}} as its deity.
{{disambiguation}}
